libircclient
------------------------------------------
Libircclient is a small but extremely powerful library which implements the
client IRC protocol. It is designed to be small, fast, portable and compatible
with the RFC standards as well as non-standard but popular features. It is
perfect for building the IRC clients and bots.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.2-1
  libircclient-devel-1.10-1bl2
  libircclient1-1.10-1bl2
  libssl1.1-1.1.1d-1
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  gcc-objc-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-7
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.ulduzsoft.com/libircclient/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/libircclient/libircclient-1.10.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libircclient-1.10-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libircclient-1.10-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libircclient-1.10-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libircclient-1.10-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libircclient1-1.10-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libircclient-devel-1.10-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libircclient)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libircclient.README
  /usr/share/doc/libircclient/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libircclient/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libircclient/README
  /usr/share/doc/libircclient/THANKS

(libircclient1)
  /usr/bin/cygircclient-1.dll

(libircclient-devel)
  /usr/include/libirc_errors.h
  /usr/include/libirc_events.h
  /usr/include/libirc_options.h
  /usr/include/libirc_rfcnumeric.h
  /usr/include/libircclient.h
  /usr/lib/libircclient.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libircclient.pc
  /usr/share/man/man1/libircclient.1.gz

